Edmond Van Daële https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edmond_Van_Da%C3%ABle 0 Edmond Van Daële (11 August 1884, Paris – 11 March 1960, Grez-Neuville, Maine-et-Loire, France) was a Dutch-French film actor. Born as Edmond Jean Adolphe Minckwitz, he appeared in the 1923 silent film Coeur fidèle, directed by Jean Epstein. He starred in nearly 50 films including Abel Gance's Napoleon between 1915 and 1950.
